ertfordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"Abt 1335–1411":"about 1335–1411","1310–Female":"1310–Deceased","1370–1455":"1370–1455","1335–1411":"1335–1411","about 1370":"about 1370","1335":"1335","1411":"1411","1455":"1455","1310":"1310","Abt 1335":"about 1335","1370":"1370","Alfold, Surrey, England":"Alfold, Surrey, England","Weld Manor, Hertfordshire":"Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Ashe","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Irish and English: variant of   Ash   1, found mainly in Ireland.","Americanized form (translation into English) of French   Dufresne  , a variant of   Ash   2.","History: This is the name of a prominent NC family; John Baptist Ashe settled in NC before 1720. It is not known where he came from: his personal name suggests that he may have been of French extraction, perhaps originally named Jean-Baptiste Dufresne."],"variants":[{"name":"Ash","meanings":["English: from Middle English <i>asche</i> ‘ash tree’ (Old English <i>æsc</i>), hence a topographic name for someone living by an ash tree or a habitational name from any of the many places in southern and central England named with this word (Derbyshire, Dorset, Hampshire, Herefordshire, Kent, Surrey, Shropshire, Somerset, and elsewhere).","Americanized form of German   Asch   and   Esch  , the latter ultimately also of Swiss German origin (see   Oesch  ).","Americanized form (translation into English) of French   Dufresne  , with the same meaning as 1 above."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Ashe was born about 1335. He married Margery Somersham about 1333, in Middlesex, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1411, in Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 77."},"et":{"Abt 1335–1411":"umbes 1335–1411","1310–Female":"1310–Surnud","1370–1455":"1370–1455","1335–1411":"1335–1411","about 1370":"umbes 1370","1335":"1335","1411":"1411","1455":"1455","1310":"1310","Abt 1335":"umbes 1335","1370":"1370","Alfold, Surrey, England":"Alfold, Surrey, England","Weld Manor, Hertfordshire":"Hertfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1335–1411":"noin 1335–1411","1310–Female":"1310–Kuollut","1370–1455":"1370–1455","1335–1411":"1335–1411","about 1370":"noin 1370","1335":"1335","1411":"1411","1455":"1455","1310":"1310","Abt 1335":"noin 1335","1370":"1370","Alfold, Surrey, England":"Alfold, Surrey, England","Weld Manor, Hertfordshire":"Hertfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1335–1411":"environ 1335–1411","1310–Female":"1310–Décédée","1370–1455":"1370–1455","1335–1411":"1335–1411","about 1370":"environ 1370","1335":"1335","1411":"1411","1455":"1455","1310":"1310","Abt 1335":"environ 1335","1370":"1370","Alfold, Surrey, England":"Alfold, Surrey, Angleterre","Weld Manor, Hertfordshire":"Hertfordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"William Ashe est né environ 1335. Il a épousé Margery Somersham environ 1333, à Middlesex, Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille. Il est décédé en 1411, à Hertfordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 77 ans."},"de":{"Abt 1335–1411":"um 1335–1411","1310–Female":"1310–Verstorben","1370–1455":"1370–1455